{"questionId":"9071356","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>Nuclear power is another source of energy.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p><sup>235</sup>U atoms can be used in nuclear reactors whereas <sup>238</sup>U cannot. A centrifuge is used&nbsp;to separate isotopes.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>Calculate the relative rate of effusion of <sup>235</sup>UF<sub>6</sub>(g) to <sup>238</sup>UF<sub>6</sub>(g) using sections&nbsp;1 and 6 of the data booklet.</p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p><em>M</em><sub>r</sub>(<sup>235</sup>UF<sub>6</sub>) =&nbsp;235 +&nbsp;(19.00 × 6)/349</p>\n<p><strong><em>OR</em></strong></p>\n<p><em>M</em><sub>r</sub>(<sup>238</sup>UF<sub>6</sub>) =&nbsp;238 +&nbsp;(19.00 × 6)/352</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>«</strong><span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"\\frac{{{\\text{rate of effusion of}}{{\\text{ }}^{235}}{\\text{U}}}}{{{\\text{rate of effusion of}}{{\\text{ }}^{238}}{\\text{U}}}} = \\sqrt {\\frac{{352}}{{349}}} &nbsp;= \">\n  <mfrac>\n    <mrow>\n      <mrow>\n        <mtext>rate of effusion of</mtext>\n      </mrow>\n      <mrow>\n        <msup>\n          <mrow>\n            <mtext>&nbsp;</mtext>\n          </mrow>\n          <mrow>\n            <mn>235</mn>\n          </mrow>\n        </msup>\n      </mrow>\n      <mrow>\n        <mtext>U</mtext>\n      </mrow>\n    </mrow>\n    <mrow>\n      <mrow>\n        <mtext>rate of effusion of</mtext>\n      </mrow>\n      <mrow>\n        <msup>\n          <mrow>\n            <mtext>&nbsp;</mtext>\n          </mrow>\n          <mrow>\n            <mn>238</mn>\n          </mrow>\n        </msup>\n      </mrow>\n      <mrow>\n        <mtext>U</mtext>\n      </mrow>\n    </mrow>\n  </mfrac>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <msqrt>\n    <mfrac>\n      <mrow>\n        <mn>352</mn>\n      </mrow>\n      <mrow>\n        <mn>349</mn>\n      </mrow>\n    </mfrac>\n  </msqrt>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n</math></span><strong>»</strong> 1.004</p>\n<p